            <h2 itemprop="headline">Understanding XML Parsing Internals</h2>
            <div class="meta">
              <time itemprop="datePublished" datetime="2025-03-31T10:00:00Z">March 31, 2025</time>
              <span class="separator">·</span>
              <span itemprop="author" itemscope="" itemtype="https://schema.org/Person">
                <span itemprop="name">Jane Doe</span>
              </span>
              <span class="separator">·</span>
              <span class="reading-time">8 min read</span>
            </div>
          </header>

          <div itemprop="articleBody">
            <p>XML parsing involves several distinct phases. The <dfn>lexer</dfn> breaks the input
              into tokens, while the <dfn>parser</dfn> assembles those tokens into a tree structure.
              Let's explore how each phase works.</p>

            <h3>Phase 1: Lexical Analysis</h3>
            <p>The lexer scans the input character-by-character, identifying:</p>
            <dl>
              <dt>Open tags</dt>
              <dd>Sequences matching <code>&lt;tagName</code> followed by optional attributes and <code>&gt;</code></dd>
              <dt>Close tags</dt>
              <dd>Sequences matching <code>&lt;/tagName&gt;</code></dd>
              <dt>Self-closing tags</dt>
              <dd>Tags ending with <code>/&gt;</code> like <code>&lt;br/&gt;</code></dd>
              <dt>Text content</dt>
              <dd>Any content between tags</dd>
              <dt>Comments</dt>
              <dd>Content wrapped in <code>&lt;!-- ... --&gt;</code></dd>
              <dt>CDATA sections</dt>
              <dd>Raw content in <code>&lt;![CDATA[ ... ]]&gt;</code></dd>
              <dt>Processing instructions</dt>
              <dd>Directives like <code>&lt;?xml version="1.0"?&gt;</code></dd>
            </dl>

            <h3>Phase 2: Tree Construction</h3>
            <p>Once tokens are identified, the parser maintains a <em>stack</em> of open elements.
              Each open tag pushes onto the stack; each close tag pops and validates.</p>

            <aside class="callout" role="note">
              <p><strong>Note:</strong> Self-closing tags (configured via <code>selfClosingTags</code>)
                never push onto the stack. They're immediately completed.</p>
            </aside>

            <h3>Phase 3: Streaming Considerations</h3>
            <p>When parsing incrementally via <code>XmlParseStream</code>, we face an additional
              challenge: the input arrives in arbitrary chunks. A single XML element might span
              multiple chunks. The parser handles this by:</p>
            <ol>
              <li>Buffering incoming chunks</li>
              <li>Scanning for the next <code>&lt;</code> character</li>
              <li>Attempting to parse a complete node from that position</li>
              <li>Only emitting the node if the parser consumed data within bounds</li>
              <li>Deferring incomplete nodes until more data arrives</li>
            </ol>

            <!-- Diagram rendered as structured data -->
            <figure id="fig-pipeline">
              <div class="diagram" aria-label="Parser pipeline diagram">
                <div class="stage" data-step="1">
                  <span class="label">Input</span>
                  <span class="desc">Raw XML string chunks</span>
                </div>
                <div class="stage" data-step="2">
                  <span class="label">Buffer</span>
                  <span class="desc">Concatenated pending data</span>
                </div>
                <div class="stage" data-step="3">
                  <span class="label">Scanner</span>
                  <span class="desc">Find next &lt; boundary</span>
                </div>
                <div class="stage" data-step="4">
                  <span class="label">Parser</span>
                  <span class="desc">parseNode() with setPos</span>
                </div>
                <div class="stage" data-step="5">
                  <span class="label">Output</span>
                  <span class="desc">TNode emitted downstream</span>
                </div>
              </div>
              <figcaption>Figure 1: The streaming XML parser pipeline</figcaption>
            </figure>
